Feature Engineering

In[7]:
# Ensure datetime, sort, set index, enforce daily frequency
df["date_day"] = pd.to_datetime(df["date_day"])
df = df.sort_values("date_day").set_index("date_day").asfreq("D")

# ---- Calendar variables (use index) ----
df["dayofweek"] = df.index.dayofweek          # 0=Mon
df["is_weekend"] = df["dayofweek"].isin([5, 6]).astype(int)
df["week"] = df.index.isocalendar().week.astype(int)
df["day"]   = df.index.day
df["month"] = df.index.month
df["year"] = df.index.year

# ---- Weather-derived variables ----
df["temp_range"] = df["tmax"] - df["tmin"]
df["is_hot"] = (df["tmed"] >= 30).astype(int)
df["is_cold"] = (df["tmed"] <= 6).astype(int)

df["is_rain"] = (df["prec"] >= 1.0).astype(int)
df["is_heavy_rain"] = (df["prec"] >= 5.0).astype(int)

# ---- Lags (now truly days) ----
df["revenue_lag_14"] = df["total_revenue"].shift(14)

df["invoices_lag_14"] = df["count_invoices"].shift(14)

# Reset date_day as a column:
df = df.reset_index().rename(columns={"date_day": "date_day"})  # keeps same name
In[8]:
# Special Y capped values # 
df["total_revenue_raw"] = df["total_revenue"]
df["total_revenue"] = df["total_revenue"].clip(upper=3500)
In[9]:
# Remomve Lags NA * 28 days of revenue and invoice counts *
df = df.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)

Seasonal Cycle with 30 Days Average

In[12]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from calendar import mdays, month_abbr

# --- 0) Prepare a daily time index ---
dfc = df.copy()
dfc["date_day"] = pd.to_datetime(dfc["date_day"])
dfc = dfc.sort_values("date_day").set_index("date_day")

# Optional (recommended if you suspect missing dates):
# dfc = dfc.asfreq("D")

# --- 1) 30-day centered rolling mean series ---
roll30 = dfc["total_revenue"].rolling(window=30, center=True, min_periods=20).mean()

# --- 2) Seasonal cycle by day-of-year (mean + IQR band) ---
seas_cycl = roll30.groupby(roll30.index.dayofyear).mean()
q25 = roll30.groupby(roll30.index.dayofyear).quantile(0.25)
q75 = roll30.groupby(roll30.index.dayofyear).quantile(0.75)

# --- 3) X-axis ticks at MONTH STARTS (day-of-year units), leap-year axis (1..366) ---
ndays_m = list(mdays)     # mdays[1..12]
ndays_m[2] = 29           # force Feb=29 so axis is 366 days

# month starts: Jan=1, Feb=32, Mar=61, ..., Dec=336  (12 values)
month_starts = [1, 32, 61, 92, 122, 153, 183, 214, 245, 275, 306, 336]
month_labels = month_abbr[1:]  # ["Jan", ..., "Dec"]

# --- 4) Plot ---
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))

ax.plot(seas_cycl.index.values, seas_cycl.values, lw=2, color="k")

ax.fill_between(
    seas_cycl.index.values,
    q25.reindex(seas_cycl.index).values.astype(float),
    q75.reindex(seas_cycl.index).values.astype(float),
    color="0.8"
)

ax.set_xticks(month_starts)
ax.set_xticklabels(month_labels)
ax.set_xlim(1, 366)  # prevents any "before January" space

ax.grid(ls=":")
ax.set_xlabel("")
ax.set_ylabel("Total revenue ()", fontsize=15)

[l.set_fontsize(13) for l in ax.xaxis.get_ticklabels()]
[l.set_fontsize(13) for l in ax.yaxis.get_ticklabels()]

ax.set_title("Seasonal cycle: 30-day running average of daily revenue", fontsize=15)

plt.tight_layout()

# --- 5) Save (optional) ---
for ext in ["png", "jpeg", "pdf"]:
    f.savefig(f"3.Outputs/seasonal_cycle_revenue.{ext}", dpi=200)

plt.show()

# --- Prepare time series ---
dfc = df.copy()
dfc["date_day"] = pd.to_datetime(dfc["date_day"])

data = dfc["total_revenue"]

# --- Plot ---
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 8))

# Daily values
data.plot(ax=ax, color="0.2")

# 30-day running average

    ax=ax, ls="-", lw=3, color="red"

# Get last known date
last_date = future_df["date_day"].max()

# Create next 14 dates
future_dates = pd.date_range(
    start=last_date + pd.Timedelta(days=1),
    periods=14,
    freq="D"
)

# Build future rows dataframe
future_rows = pd.DataFrame({
    "date_day": future_dates
})

# Add calendar features
future_rows["day"] = future_rows["date_day"].dt.day
future_rows["month"] = future_rows["date_day"].dt.month

# Add empty placeholders for unknown future values
future_rows["count_invoices"] = np.nan
future_rows["total_revenue"] = np.nan

# Append to existing future_df
future_df = pd.concat([future_df, future_rows], ignore_index=True)

Model: Prophet

Train-Test split and Prophet variables: "ds" and "y"

In[25]:
# ---- Choose your windows here (YYYY-MM) ----
train_start = "2022-01"
train_end   = "2025-12"

# ---- Convert to actual date boundaries ----
train_start_date = pd.to_datetime(train_start + "-01")
train_end_date   = pd.to_datetime(train_end + "-01") + pd.offsets.MonthEnd(1)

# ---- Ensure datetime + sort ----
df2 = df.copy()
df2["date_day"] = pd.to_datetime(df2["date_day"])
df2 = df2.sort_values("date_day")

# ---- Split (still using your original date_day) ----
train_df = df2[(df2["date_day"] >= train_start_date) & (df2["date_day"] <= train_end_date)].copy()

# ---- Prophet column names ----
# Keep your regressors in predictor_cols (must exist in both train_df and test_df)
train_p = train_df.rename(columns={"date_day": "ds", "total_revenue": "y"}).copy()

# Optional safety checks
train_p["ds"] = pd.to_datetime(train_p["ds"])

print("Train ds range:", train_p["ds"].min(), "", train_p["ds"].max())

from matplotlib.gridspec import GridSpec

def joint_plot_pred_obs(
    verif: pd.DataFrame,
    pred_col: str = "pred",
    obs_col: str = "obs",
    title: str = "set",
    bins: int = 30,
    fname: str | None = None
):
    # Drop missing
    d = verif[[pred_col, obs_col]].dropna().copy()
    x = d[pred_col].values
    y = d[obs_col].values

    # Metrics
    mae = np.mean(np.abs(y - x))
    r = np.corrcoef(x, y)[0, 1] if len(d) > 1 else np.nan

    # Regression line (simple least squares)
    if len(d) > 1:
        b1, b0 = np.polyfit(x, y, 1)  # y = b1*x + b0
        xline = np.linspace(x.min(), x.max(), 200)
        yline = b1 * xline + b0
    else:
        xline = yline = None

    # Layout: top histogram + main scatter + right histogram
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    gs = GridSpec(4, 4, figure=fig, hspace=0.05, wspace=0.05)

    ax_top   = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, 0:3])
    ax_main  = fig.add_subplot(gs[1:4, 0:3])
    ax_right = fig.add_subplot(gs[1:4, 3])

    # --- Main scatter ---
    ax_main.scatter(x, y, s=18, alpha=0.65, color="0.35", edgecolors="none")

    # --- Perfect prediction (45-degree) line ---
    xy_min = min(x.min(), y.min())
    xy_max = max(x.max(), y.max())
    
    ax_main.plot(
        [xy_min, xy_max],
        [xy_min, xy_max],
        ls="--",
        lw=2,
        color="0.4",
        alpha=0.9,
        zorder=0,
        label="Perfect prediction"
    )

    # Regression line + light band (visual only)
    if xline is not None:
        ax_main.plot(xline, yline, color="0.25", lw=2)
        # simple constant band based on residual std (not a formal CI)
        resid = y - (b1 * x + b0)
        s = np.std(resid)
        ax_main.fill_between(xline, yline - 1.0*s, yline + 1.0*s, color="0.7", alpha=0.25, linewidth=0)

    ax_main.grid(ls=":", alpha=0.6)
    ax_main.set_xlabel("model's estimates", fontsize=12)
    ax_main.set_ylabel("observations", fontsize=12)
    ax_main.set_title(title, fontsize=13, pad=10)

    # Metrics text (top-left inside main panel)
    ax_main.text(
        0.05, 0.92,
        f"R = {r:+.2f}\nMAE = {mae:.1f}",
        transform=ax_main.transAxes,
        fontsize=12,
        va="top"
    )

    # --- Top histogram (pred) ---
    ax_top.hist(x, bins=bins, color="0.75", edgecolor="0.35", density=True)
    ax_top.set_ylabel("")
    ax_top.tick_params(axis="x", labelbottom=False)
    ax_top.grid(False)
    for spine in ["right", "top", "left"]:
        ax_top.spines[spine].set_visible(False)

    # --- Right histogram (obs) ---
    ax_right.hist(y, bins=bins, orientation="horizontal", color="0.75", edgecolor="0.35", density=True)
    ax_right.tick_params(axis="y", labelleft=False)
    ax_right.grid(False)
    for spine in ["right", "top", "bottom"]:
        ax_right.spines[spine].set_visible(False)

    # Clean shared limits (optional but makes it nicer)
    xmin, xmax = np.nanmin(x), np.nanmax(x)
    ymin, ymax = np.nanmin(y), np.nanmax(y)
    ax_main.set_xlim(xmin, xmax)
    ax_main.set_ylim(min(ymin, xmin), max(ymax, xmax))

    plt.tight_layout()

    if fname:
        fig.savefig(f"3.Outputs/{fname}.png", dpi=200, bbox_inches="tight")

    return fig

Residual Distribution (train set)












In[57]:






# Merge predictions with actuals (test set)
verif_train = train_p[["ds", "y"]].merge(
    forecast_train[["ds", "yhat"]],
    on="ds",
    how="left"
)

# Residuals: model - observed (same sign convention as your example)
residuals = verif_train["yhat"] - verif_train["y"]

# Absolute errors
abs_errors = residuals.abs()

# ---- Metrics ----
MAE = abs_errors.mean()
RMSE = np.sqrt((residuals ** 2).mean())

# Avoid division by zero in MAPE
mape_mask = verif_train["y"] != 0
MAPE = (abs_errors[mape_mask] / verif_train.loc[mape_mask, "y"]).mean() * 100

Q95_abs_error = abs_errors.quantile(0.95)

# ---- Print results ----
print("Test set performance metrics")
print("-" * 35)
print(f"MAE              : {MAE:8.2f}")
print(f"RMSE             : {RMSE:8.2f}")
print(f"MAPE (%)         : {MAPE:8.2f}")
print(f"95% abs. error   : {Q95_abs_error:8.2f}")

In[69]:






def make_plot_block(verif, start_date, end_date, ax=None):
    start = pd.to_datetime(start_date)
    end   = pd.to_datetime(end_date)

    df = verif.loc[start:end].copy()

    ax.plot(df.index, df["yhat"], lw=2, color="red", label="forecasts")
    ax.fill_between(
        df.index,
        df["yhat_lower"].astype(float),
        df["yhat_upper"].astype(float),
        color="coral", alpha=0.3
    )
    ax.plot(df.index, df["y"], lw=2, color="steelblue", label="observations")

    ax.set_xlim(start, end)   #  datetime, not strings
    ax.grid(ls=":")
    ax.legend(fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel("Total revenue ()", fontsize=14)
    ax.set_xlabel("")
    ax.set_title(f"Train set: {start_date} to {end_date}", fontsize=16)

    [l.set_fontsize(12) for l in ax.xaxis.get_ticklabels()]
    [l.set_fontsize(12) for l in ax.yaxis.get_ticklabels()]

Combine Scenarios












In[91]:






# Keep only what you need from each forecast + rename yhat
pred_base = forecast_1[["ds", "yhat"]].rename(columns={"yhat": "yhat_baseline"})
pred_low  = forecast_2[["ds", "yhat"]].rename(columns={"yhat": "yhat_lowcxf"})
pred_high = forecast_3[["ds", "yhat"]].rename(columns={"yhat": "yhat_highcxf"})

# Merge on ds (inner keeps only dates present in all 3 forecasts)
pred_all = (
    pred_base
    .merge(pred_low, on="ds", how="inner")
    .merge(pred_high, on="ds", how="inner")
    .sort_values("ds")
    .reset_index(drop=True)
)

# Ensure order is correct (sometimes low/high can cross if scenario effect is non-monotonic)
band_low  = pred_all[["yhat_lowcxf", "yhat_highcxf"]].min(axis=1)
band_high = pred_all[["yhat_lowcxf", "yhat_highcxf"]].max(axis=1)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))

# Band
plt.fill_between(
    pred_all["ds"],
    band_low,
    band_high,
    alpha=0.2
)

# Baseline line
plt.plot(pred_all["ds"], pred_all["yhat_baseline"], marker="o")

plt.title("Forecast scenarios: baseline with lowhigh band")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Predicted y (yhat)")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Importar libreras
from joblib import dump
import sklearn, prophet

#####################################################################################################################################
# Crear un diccionario llamado model_bundle que contiene el m (en este caso un modelo ajustado por Prophet), una lista de regresores#
# el nombre date_col y un metadiccionario con diversos detalles sobre la creacin del modelo y las estrategias utilizadas,          #
# junto con las versiones de las bibliotecas clave. Pide ayuda a la IA para definir esta variable exactamente para el modelo        #
# que has entrenado, a partir del cdigo que has escrito.                                                                           #
#####################################################################################################################################

model_bundle = {
    "model": m,                      # Prophet fitted model
    "regressors": regressors,        # list of regressor names expected at predict time
    "date_col": "ds",
    "meta": {
        "created_at": "2026-01-28",
        "horizon_days": 14,
        "visitantes_strategy": "weekly_mean_by_dow",
        "weather_strategy": "doy_climatology",
        "lags_strategy": "asfreq_daily_missing_as_closed_zero",
        "sklearn_version": getattr(sklearn, "__version__", None),
        "prophet_version": getattr(prophet, "__version__", None),
        "pandas_version": getattr(pd, "__version__", None),
    }
}

# UtilizaR la funcin joblib.dump para guardar este diccionario model_bundle en la ruta especificada e imprime un mensaje de confirmacin
dump(model_bundle, "3.Outputs/2026_02_01_prophet_total_revenue_model.joblib")
